name: Saraswati - cerise
description:
Tiny Japanese beads on silk thread with an adjustable clasp
Extends from 13 to 20 cm (5-8")
White with cerise, gold charm

Goddess of Knowledge & Arts
Saraswati is the goddess of knowledge and arts and represents the free flow of wisdom and consciousness. 
She helps with speech, wisdom and learning. Often depicted with four hands, she hold sacred scripture in one and a lotus, symboising true knowledge in another. With her other two hands she plays the music of love and life on a string instrument called the veena. She is dressed in white, the symbol of purityand rides on a white swan, symbolizing Sattwa Guna or purity and discernment.
